# ⚡ Test Electra — Electronics Store Website

A fictional electronics store website built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Fully static — no build tools, no dependencies, ready to deploy on GitHub Pages in minutes.

## Sections

- **Home** — Hero with animated visuals and stats
- **Products** — 12 fictional products with category filtering
- **Services** — 6 service offerings (repair, custom PC, smart home, etc.)
- **About** — Brand story, values, and team
- **FAQ** — 8 accordion questions

## Deploying to GitHub Pages

1. Create a new repository on GitHub (e.g. `test-electra`)
2. Upload all files keeping the folder structure:
   ```
   index.html
   css/style.css
   js/main.js
   README.md
   ```
3. Go to **Settings → Pages**
4. Under **Source**, select `main` branch and `/ (root)` folder
5. Click **Save** — your site will be live at `https://yourusername.github.io/test-electra/`

## Tech Stack

- Pure HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- Google Fonts: Space Grotesk + Space Mono
- Zero external dependencies
- Responsive down to 320px
- Accessible (keyboard navigation, ARIA labels, reduced motion support)

## Customisation

All design tokens (colors, fonts, spacing) are in CSS custom properties at the top of `css/style.css`. Product data lives in the `products` array at the top of `js/main.js`.

---

*This is a fictional store created for demonstration/portfolio purposes. All brand names, prices, and products are invented.*
